# Project context: social_graph (Netgraph)

- Next.js 16 / React 19 / TypeScript / Tailwind / `react-force-graph-2d`.
- Optional Vercel KV for cache, Vercel Blob for pinned snapshots.
- Currently running in **demo/dummy-data mode** because Apify credits are insufficient.
- Do not add new live Apify calls or assume `APIFY_TOKEN` is available.

## Data sources

- Live graph pages (`/graph/[handle]`) use `getNetwork` in `lib/scrape.ts`. It falls back to deterministic mock data from `lib/mock.ts` when `APIFY_TOKEN` is unset.
- Pinned pages (`/graph/[handle]/pinned`) serve static snapshots via `lib/snapshot.ts` (disk or Blob). They do not call Apify.
- Existing tracked snapshot: `data/snapshots/diandra.json`, imported from `data/raw/diandra_linkedin_scrape_71226.json`.
- Instagram demo companion: `data/snapshots/jppap.json` from `data/insta_raw/jp_jppap.json` (loaded on pinned pages via the Instagram platform tab).
- Spotify demo companion: `data/snapshots/sebastian-spotify.json` from Sebastian’s profile + Schmok playlist scrapes (loaded via the Spotify platform tab).
- Deployed reference URL: `https://social-graph-nu.vercel.app/graph/diandra/pinned`.

## Guardrails

- If a task would require real Instagram scraping, warn the user and suggest using dummy data or importing a raw comment export instead.
- Keep existing snapshot files in place unless the user explicitly asks to replace them.
- If replacing a pinned snapshot, regenerate it from mock data or an imported export so the pinned page stays Apify-free.
